## DuplicateFunctionArguments

**Severity:** warning | **Type:** LiquidHtml

This check ensures that no duplicate argument names are provided when invoking a partial as a function using the `{% raw %}{% function %}{% endraw %}` tag. Duplicate argument names are almost always a mistake and can lead to unexpected behavior, since only one of the values will be used.

## Examples

### &#x2717; Incorrect Code Example (Avoid using this):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% function result = 'my_function', name: "Alice", name: "Bob" %}
{% endraw %}
```

The `name` argument is passed twice.

### &#x2713; Correct Code Example (Use this instead):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% function result = 'my_function', name: "Alice" %}
{% endraw %}
```

## Configuration

The default configuration for this check:

```yaml
DuplicateFunctionArguments:
  enabled: true
  severity: warning
```

## Disabling This Check

Disabling this check is not recommended. Duplicate arguments are always a mistake.

